# Restart app after changes

After making code or XAML changes to MabaControlCenter:

1. Close any running instance: `Get-Process -Name "MabaControlCenter" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force`
2. Wait 1 second so the process fully exits
3. Start the app: `cd C:\Users\PC\Desktop\MabaControlCenter; dotnet run`
4. Run in the background so the window opens and the user can test

Use a single command, e.g.:
`Get-Process -Name "MabaControlCenter" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force; Start-Sleep -Seconds 1; cd C:\Users\PC\Desktop\MabaControlCenter; dotnet run`
with `is_background: true` so the app stays open.
